      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A simpler solution is always preferable, especially if you're not comfortable with DIY repairs. It's possible that a worn-out capacitor, a faulty contactor, or a blown fuse could be causing the issue. These components can fail over time, much like a worn-out pair of shoes that just can't keep up with the demands of a busy day. \n\nWhen working with electrical components, it's essential to exercise caution. Make sure to unplug the unit from the power source before opening the panel, and consider wearing gloves and safety glasses to protect yourself from any potential electrical shocks or debris. You should also be mindful of the refrigerant lines, which can be under high pressure and potentially hazardous if not handled properly. It's a good idea to consult the unit's manual or online resources for specific guidance on safety procedures and component replacement.",
